    <description>SS2-T218  Runs on weekdays to check &apos;Complaint&apos; Cases with status &apos;Open&apos;. Triggers if Henkel Cases are open &gt;24 hrs or others &gt;3 days from Created Date.
In version -5, the name-value pair for the Org-Wide Email Address was retrieved and configured in the Send Email element.</description>
    <environments>Default</environments>
    <formulas>
        <name>has72HrsPassed</name>
        <dataType>Boolean</dataType>
        <expression>((NOW() - {!$Record.CreatedDate}) * 24) &gt;72</expression>
    </formulas>
    <formulas>
        <name>has_24h_Passed</name>
        <dataType>Boolean</dataType>
        <expression>((NOW() - {!$Record.CreatedDate}) * 24) &gt;=24.01</expression>
    </formulas>
    <formulas>
        <description>Base Url of the system</description>
        <name>URLBase</name>
        <dataType>String</dataType>
        <expression>LEFT({!$Api.Enterprise_Server_URL_610}, FIND(&quot;/services&quot;, {!$Api.Enterprise_Server_URL_610}) - 1)</expression>
    </formulas>
    <formulas>
        <name>varNotHENKEL</name>
        <dataType>Boolean</dataType>
        <expression>NOT(CONTAINS({!$Record.Account.Group_Key__c}, &quot;HENKEL&quot;))</expression>
    </formulas>
    <formulas>
        <name>varSubject</name>
        <dataType>String</dataType>
        <expression>&apos;Notification of No response to Customer Complaint &apos; + {!$Record.CaseNumber} + &apos;: &apos; + {!$Record.Subject}</expression>
    </formulas>
    <formulas>
        <name>varWeekDay</name>
        <dataType>Number</dataType>
        <expression>WEEKDAY(TODAY())</expression>
        <scale>0</scale>
    </formulas>
